zsh -lc \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"sed -n '1,240p' docs/r750-application-deployment-plan.md\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\" in /Users/anthony/Programming/PromptClaw\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+ succeeded in 0ms:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+# PromptClaw Application Deployment Plan — Dell PowerEdge R750\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+**Prerequisite:** The bare metal runbook (`r750-bare-metal-runbook.md`) has been completed. Ubuntu 24.04 is installed, dual Ollama instances are running on ports 11434/11435, PostgreSQL and Redis are healthy, and Tailscale is connected.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+**Goal:** Deploy PromptClaw on the R750 with Ollama as a first-class agent alongside the existing cloud CLI agents (claude, codex, gemini). No architectural rewrites — extend the existing daemon to route tasks to local models.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+---\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+## Part 1: Clone and Configure PromptClaw\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+### 1.1 Create the deployment user and directories\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+```bash\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+# Use your existing user (created during Ubuntu install), not root\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+mkdir -p ~/cypherclaw\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+mkdir -p /data/promptclaw/{observatory,sdp-state,gallery,logs,artifacts}\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+```\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+### 1.2 Clone the repository\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+```bash\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+cd ~\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+git clone https://github.com/exquest/cypherclaw-private.git cypherclaw\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+cd cypherclaw\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+```\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+> **Note:** You'll need to authenticate with GitHub. Either configure an SSH key or use a personal access token for HTTPS.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+### 1.3 Create the Python virtual environment\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+```bash\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+cd ~/cypherclaw\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+python3 -m venv .venv\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+source .venv/bin/activate\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+# Install the package and optional dependencies\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+pip install -e \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\".[coherence-pg]\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+# Install runtime dependencies used by tools\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+pip install httpx pillow psycopg2-binary redis structlog\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+```\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+### 1.4 Install cloud CLI agents\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+The daemon invokes `claude`, `codex`, and `gemini` as subprocess commands. Install them:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+```bash\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+# Claude Code CLI (Anthropic)\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+npm install -g @anthropic-ai/claude-code\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+# Codex CLI (OpenAI) — check current install method\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+npm install -g @openai/codex\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+# Gemini CLI (Google)\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+npm install -g @anthropic-ai/claude-code  # verify actual package name\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+# OR\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+pip install google-genai\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+```\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+> **Note:** These cloud CLIs require API keys. They are optional on the R750 — the whole point is to use local Ollama models for most work. But keeping them available gives you fallback capability when quota exists.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+Verify they are on PATH:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+```bash\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+which claude codex gemini 2>/dev/null\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+```\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+### 1.5 Install sdp-cli\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+```bash\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+cd ~\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+git clone <sdp-cli-repo-url> sdp-cli\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+cd sdp-cli\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+pip install -e .\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+# OR if it installs to ~/.local/bin:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+pip install --user -e .\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+```\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+Verify:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+```bash\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+which sdp-cli\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+sdp-cli --version\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+```\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+### 1.6 Create the .env file\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+```bash\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+cat > ~/cypherclaw/.env << 'ENV'\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+DB_MODE=dual\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+DATABASE_URL=postgresql://inference:YOUR_PG_PASSWORD@localhost:5432/langgraph\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN=YOUR_TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+TELEGRAM_CHAT_ID=YOUR_TELEGRAM_CHAT_ID\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+GEMINI_API_KEY=YOUR_GEMINI_API_KEY\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+# R750-specific: Ollama endpoints for dual-socket topology\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+OLLAMA_URL_SOCKET0=http://localhost:11434\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+OLLAMA_URL_SOCKET1=http://localhost:11435\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+# Default Ollama URL (used by art_engine.py and the new ollama agent)\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+OLLAMA_URL=http://localhost:11434\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+ENV\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+chmod 600 ~/cypherclaw/.env\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+```\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+> **Warning:** Copy your actual tokens from the CypherClaw `.env` file. Do NOT commit this file to git.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+### 1.7 Initialize the Observatory database\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+The R750's PostgreSQL (from the runbook) already has a `langgraph` database. Add the observatory tables:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+```bash\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+PGPASSWORD=YOUR_PG_PASSWORD psql -h localhost -U inference -d langgraph << 'SQL'\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+-- Observatory core tables (from observatory.py schema)\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS events (\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+    id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+    event_type TEXT NOT NULL,\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+    timestamp TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT NOW(),\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+    data JSONB\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+);\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS task_results (\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+    id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+    agent TEXT NOT NULL,\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+    task_id TEXT,\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+    success BOOLEAN NOT NULL,\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+    duration_ms INTEGER,\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+    tokens INTEGER,\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+    gate_pass BOOLEAN,\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+    category TEXT,\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+    timestamp TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT NOW()\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+);\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS healing_log (\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+    id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+    failure_type TEXT NOT NULL,\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+    severity TEXT,\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+    action_taken TEXT,\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+    context JSONB,\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+    timestamp TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT NOW()\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+);\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS agent_skills (\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+    id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+    agent TEXT NOT NULL,\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+    category TEXT NOT NULL,\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+    score REAL NOT NULL DEFAULT 0.5,\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+    sample_count INTEGER NOT NULL DEFAULT 0,\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+    updated_at TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT NOW(),\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+    UNIQUE(agent, category)\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+);\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS daily_rollups (\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+    id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+    agent TEXT NOT NULL,\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+    date DATE NOT NULL,\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+    tasks_completed INTEGER DEFAULT 0,\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+    tasks_failed INTEGER DEFAULT 0,\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+    tokens_used INTEGER DEFAULT 0,\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+    total_duration_ms INTEGER DEFAULT 0,\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+    gate_passes INTEGER DEFAULT 0,\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+    UNIQUE(agent, date)\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+);\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS watchdog_events (\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+    id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+    event_type TEXT NOT NULL,\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+    details JSONB,\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+    timestamp TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT NOW()\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+);\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+-- Indexes\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+CREATE INDEX IF NOT EXISTS idx_events_type_ts ON events(event_type, timestamp);\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+CREATE INDEX IF NOT EXISTS idx_task_results_agent ON task_results(agent, timestamp);\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+CREATE INDEX IF NOT EXISTS idx_agent_skills_lookup ON agent_skills(agent, category);\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+-- Seed initial skill scores for the ollama agent\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+INSERT INTO agent_skills (agent, category, score, sample_count) VALUES\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+    ('ollama', 'architecture', 0.65, 0),\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+    ('ollama', 'review', 0.60, 0),\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+    ('ollama', 'coding', 0.70, 0),\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+    ('ollama', 'research', 0.65, 0),\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+    ('ollama', 'routing', 0.70, 0),\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+    ('ollama', 'writing', 0.70, 0),\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+    ('ollama', 'testing', 0.65, 0),\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+    ('ollama', 'devops', 0.60, 0),\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+    ('ollama', 'netops', 0.80, 0)\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+ON CONFLICT (agent, category) DO NOTHING;\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+SELECT 'Observatory schema created successfully' AS status;\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+SQL\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+```\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+### 1.8 Initialize the workspace\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+```bash\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+# Create the tmpfs working directory structure\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+sudo mkdir -p /run/cypherclaw-tmp/workdir/cypherclaw-work\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+sudo chmod 1777 /run/cypherclaw-tmp\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+# Initialize SDP state directories\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+mkdir -p ~/cypherclaw/.sdp\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+mkdir -p ~/cypherclaw/.promptclaw\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+# Create symlinks to persistent storage\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+ln -sf /data/promptclaw/observatory ~/cypherclaw/.promptclaw/db\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+ln -sf /data/promptclaw/sdp-state ~/cypherclaw/.sdp/persistent\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+```\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+---\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+## Part 2: Add Ollama as a First-Class Agent\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+This is the core integration work. The changes are minimal because the daemon's architecture already supports pluggable agents.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+### 2.1 Modify agent_selector.py\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+Add Ollama to the provider map and fitness scores:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+```python\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+# In agent_selector.py\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+PROVIDERS = {\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+    \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"claude\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"anthropic\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+    \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"codex\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"openai\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+    \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"gemini\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"google\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+    \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"ollama\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"local\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",       # <-- ADD\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+}\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+DEFAULT_FITNESS = {\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+    \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"claude\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": {\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"architecture\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": 0.85, \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"review\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": 0.90, \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"coding\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": 0.70, ...},\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+    \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"codex\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": {\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"architecture\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": 0.55, \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"review\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": 0.60, \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"coding\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": 0.90, ...},\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+    \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"gemini\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": {\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"architecture\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": 0.60, \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"review\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": 0.55, \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"coding\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": 0.55, ...},\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+    \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"ollama\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": {                                                    # <-- ADD\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+        \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"architecture\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": 0.65,\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+        \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"review\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": 0.60,\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+        \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"coding\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": 0.70,\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+        \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"research\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": 0.65,\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+exec\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+/bin/zsh -lc \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"sed -n '1,220p' AGENTS.md\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\" in /Users/anthony/Programming/PromptClaw\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+ succeeded in 0ms:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+# AGENTS.md\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+This is the single source of truth for all agents working on PromptClaw projects. CLAUDE.md points here. All agents (Claude, Codex, Gemini, local LLMs) read this file.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+## Core Tenets\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+### 1. Test-Driven Development (TDD)\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+- Write tests BEFORE or ALONGSIDE implementation — never after\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+- No module ships without corresponding tests\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+- If fixing a bug, write a failing test first, then fix\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+- Mock external services in tests\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+### 2. Verify/Scan/Fix Loop\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+After every action: verify it worked, scan for side effects, fix anything found, repeat until clean. Never leave broken things behind.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+### 3. Read Before You Write\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+Read existing code and the relevant PRD before modifying anything.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+## Working rules\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+- Prefer the standard library.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+- Keep new modules small and typed.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+- Treat `README.md` and `docs/` as product-facing documentation.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+- Treat `.promptclaw/` as runtime state, not source.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+- Do not hardcode provider secrets or agent commands in source files.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+- When changing orchestration behavior, update:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+  - `docs/architecture.md`\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+  - `docs/handoff-protocol.md`\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+  - `docs/command-reference.md`\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+  - `docs/startup-wizard.md`\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+  - `CHANGELOG.md`\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+## Runtime contract\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+- Handoffs happen through files inside `.promptclaw/runs/<run-id>/`.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+- The orchestrator may ask the user questions only when the task is ambiguous.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+- Startup onboarding happens through the wizard or the starter prompts.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+- Lead and verifier should be different agents whenever possible.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+exec\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+/bin/zsh -lc 'rg -n \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"ADP|Application Deployment|Explore|Specify|Test|Implement|Verify|Document\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\" docs sdp specs AGENTS.md README.md' in /Users/anthony/Programming/PromptClaw\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+ succeeded in 0ms:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+AGENTS.md:7:### 1. Test-Driven Development (TDD)\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+AGENTS.md:13:### 2. Verify/Scan/Fix Loop\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+README.md:92:promptclaw run . --task \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"Implement user authentication\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+specs/t-010@20260408t223256zb-spec.md:15:4. **Integration test** — Test that `/status` output includes Ollama health text when `ollama_health()` returns healthy/unhealthy instances, and that the heartbeat payload contains the `\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"ollama\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"` key.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+specs/t-021@20260416t043834z-spec.md:69:  composition task. Documented in ESCALATIONS.md.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+specs/t-021@20260416t043834z-spec.md:75:   VERIFY: `pytest tests/test_self_critique.py::TestPreviewScore -q`\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+specs/t-021@20260416t043834z-spec.md:78:   VERIFY: `pytest tests/test_self_critique.py::TestReviseScore::test_revision_requested_for_failed_metrics -q`\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+specs/t-021@20260416t043834z-spec.md:80:3. Tests verify rewrite improves at least one target metric without changing piece\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+specs/t-021@20260416t043834z-spec.md:82:   VERIFY: `pytest tests/test_self_critique.py::TestReviseScore::test_revision_improves_at_least_one_metric -q`\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+specs/t-021@20260416t043834z-spec.md:85:   VERIFY: `pytest tests/test_self_critique.py::TestReviseScore::test_identity_preserved_after_revision -q`\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+specs/t-021@20260416t043834z-spec.md:88:   VERIFY: `pytest tests/test_self_critique.py::TestReviseScore::test_no_revision_when_passing -q`\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+specs/t-021@20260416t043834z-spec.md:91:   VERIFY: `pytest tests/test_self_critique.py::TestReviseScore::test_keeps_original_when_revision_worse -q`\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+specs/t-021@20260416t043834z-spec.md:94:   VERIFY: `pytest tests/test_self_critique.py::TestReviseScore::test_max_one_rewrite_pass -q`\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+sdp/notifications.log:201:{\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"agent\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"claude\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\", \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"duration\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": 3375.528, \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"event\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"task_escalated\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\", \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"outcome\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"escalated\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\", \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"summary\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"Verify model rejected by provider: The verify model was rejected by the provider CLI. This is a configuration error, not a code issue. Fix the model ID and re-run. Error: OpenAI Codex v0.120.0 (research preview)\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n--------\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nworkdir: /Users/anthony/Programming/PromptClaw\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nmodel: gpt-5.3-codex-spark\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nprovider: openai\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\napproval: never\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nsandbox: danger-full-access\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nreasoning effor...\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\", \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"task_id\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"T-022@20260416T043834Z\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\", \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"timestamp\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"2026-04-16T12:14:34.979335+00:00\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"}\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+sdp/task-graph.md:16:| 4 | T-004 | Implement critical-listening and psychoacoustic interpretation rules. | T1 | 2 | 3 | MPC-013 | — | - ear engine or production evaluator exposes spectral balance, dynamic contour, spatial distribution, timbral quality, rhythmic activity, harmonic tension, masking risk, and equal-loudness compensation hints<br/>- feedback can modify future density, register, EQ, dynamics, and sound-palette choices<br/>- tests use synthetic events/audio features to verify correction decisions |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+sdp/task-graph.md:18:| 6 | T-006 | Implement ensemble-space and Theramini partner behavior from the course. | T1 | 3 | 3 | MPC-015 | — | - policy supports listening first, complementary register, rhythmic sympathy, harmonic response intervals, accompaniment textures, call/response, imitation, commentary, completion, and silence<br/>- score/tracker metadata identifies current lead/support roles<br/>- tests verify no register crowding, no excessive overlap during human/Theramini gesture, and recovery to solo mode |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+sdp/task-graph.md:44:| 14 | T-014 | Implement a verified pitch, interval, scale, and mode library. | T1 | 2 | 3 | MPC-002 | T-001 | - library includes chromatic, major/minor, seven modes, pentatonic, whole-tone, octatonic, blues, Hirajoshi, In Sen, Pelog, Bhairav, Hungarian minor, Prometheus, and microtonal/ratio helpers<br/>- interval metadata includes semitones, consonance/dissonance, character, and arc-phase affinity<br/>- tests verify interval/scale pitch-class sets and MIDI/frequency conversion |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+sdp/requirements-register.md:9:| MPC-002 | Implement a verified pitch, interval, scale, and mode library. | MUST | T1 |  |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+sdp/requirements-register.md:20:| MPC-013 | Implement critical-listening and psychoacoustic interpretation rules. | MUST | T1 |  |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+sdp/requirements-register.md:22:| MPC-015 | Implement ensemble-space and Theramini partner behavior from the course. | MUST | T1 |  |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+sdp/prd-snapshot.md:70:### Implemented Foundation\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+sdp/prd-snapshot.md:132:| MPC-002 | Implement a verified pitch, interval, scale, and mode library. | MUST | T1 | - library includes chromatic, major/minor, seven modes, pentatonic, whole-tone, octatonic, blues, Hirajoshi, In Sen, Pelog, Bhairav, Hungarian minor, Prometheus, and microtonal/ratio helpers<br/>- interval metadata includes semitones, consonance/dissonance, character, and arc-phase affinity<br/>- tests verify interval/scale pitch-class sets and MIDI/frequency conversion |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+sdp/prd-snapshot.md:143:| MPC-013 | Implement critical-listening and psychoacoustic interpretation rules. | MUST | T1 | - ear engine or production evaluator exposes spectral balance, dynamic contour, spatial distribution, timbral quality, rhythmic activity, harmonic tension, masking risk, and equal-loudness compensation hints<br/>- feedback can modify future density, register, EQ, dynamics, and sound-palette choices<br/>- tests use synthetic events/audio features to verify correction decisions |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+sdp/prd-snapshot.md:145:| MPC-015 | Implement ensemble-space and Theramini partner behavior from the course. | MUST | T1 | - policy supports listening first, complementary register, rhythmic sympathy, harmonic response intervals, accompaniment textures, call/response, imitation, commentary, completion, and silence<br/>- score/tracker metadata identifies current lead/support roles<br/>- tests verify no register crowding, no excessive overlap during human/Theramini gesture, and recovery to solo mode |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+sdp/prd-snapshot.md:186:## Suggested Implementation Phases\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+sdp/templates/claude/lead_t2.md:22:2. Implement the smallest viable solution first.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+sdp/run-log.md:3:| Run ID | Task | Lead | Verify | Verdict | Duration | Gates |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+sdp/templates/claude/verify.md:12:Verify by executing the change and checking outcomes. Do not write a deep design review.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+sdp/templates/claude/verify.md:58:**Verify Agent:** [your agent name]\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+sdp/templates/codex/verify.md:12:Verify by executing the change and checking outcomes. Do not write a deep design review.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+sdp/templates/codex/verify.md:58:**Verify Agent:** [your agent name]\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+docs/home-visit-playbook.md:58:# Test 1: Plain text with initialize + line feed\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+docs/home-visit-playbook.md:61:# Test 2: If nothing prints, try the other device\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+docs/home-visit-playbook.md:64:# Test 3: With explicit cut\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+docs/home-visit-playbook.md:74:### Step 1.4 — Test the Python path\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+docs/home-visit-playbook.md:155:# Verify it's paused (status T)\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+docs/home-visit-playbook.md:174:# Verify\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+docs/home-visit-playbook.md:197:# Verify both files exist and have content\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+docs/home-visit-playbook.md:258:# Verify it's running again (status S)\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+sdp/templates/codex/lead_t2.md:22:2. Implement the smallest viable solution first.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+docs/cypherclaw-upgrade-checklist.md:83:Tests and checks:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+docs/cypherclaw-upgrade-checklist.md:113:Tests:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+docs/cypherclaw-upgrade-checklist.md:141:Tests:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+docs/cypherclaw-upgrade-checklist.md:194:Tests:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+docs/cypherclaw-upgrade-checklist.md:238:Tests:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+docs/cypherclaw-upgrade-checklist.md:267:Tests:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+docs/cypherclaw-upgrade-checklist.md:296:Tests:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+docs/cypherclaw-upgrade-checklist.md:324:Tests:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+docs/cypherclaw-upgrade-checklist.md:351:Tests and checks:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+docs/cypherclaw-upgrade-checklist.md:375:Tests and checks:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+docs/cypherclaw-upgrade-checklist.md:392:2. Implement locally.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+sdp/templates/gemini/lead_t3.md:23:1.  **Specify**: Create a plan of attack. Write a brief specification in `sdp/specs/{{ task_id | lower }}.md`. Outline your approach, files to be modified, and new tests to be added. Commit the spec.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+sdp/templates/gemini/lead_t3.md:24:2.  **Test**: Write the tests for the new functionality. They should fail initially. Commit the new tests.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+sdp/templates/gemini/lead_t3.md:25:3.  **Implement**: Write the code to make the tests pass. Commit the implementation.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+sdp/templates/gemini/lead_t3.md:26:4.  **Verify**: Run the full validation suite.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+docs/2026-03-28-promptclaw-discovery-phase2-report-CODEX.md:159:**C2 — ChromaDB Test:** [FAIL No module named 'chromadb']\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+docs/2026-03-28-promptclaw-discovery-phase2-report-CODEX.md:164:**C3 — FAISS Test:** [FAIL No module named 'faiss']\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+docs/2026-03-28-promptclaw-discovery-phase2-report-CODEX.md:376:- `grep -r \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"TODO\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\|FIXME\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\