** — Tests are isolated and well-structured.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+sdp/logs/Lead_T-010_20260408T223256Zb_1775693726.log:8:Read the project's ADP documentation and understand existing patterns before making changes.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+sdp/logs/Lead_T-010_20260408T223256Zb_1775693726.log:10:**ADP Phases:** Explore → Specify → Test → Implement → Verify → Document\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+sdp/logs/Lead_T-010_20260408T223256Zb_1775693726.log:12:### Phase 0: Explore\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+sdp/logs/Lead_T-010_20260408T223256Zb_1775693726.log:18:### Phase 1: Specify\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+sdp/logs/Lead_T-010_20260408T223256Zb_1775693726.log:23:### Phase 2: Test Development\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+sdp/logs/Lead_T-010_20260408T223256Zb_1775693726.log:25:- Tests must FAIL before implementation (Red phase).\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+sdp/logs/Lead_T-010_20260408T223256Zb_1775693726.log:28:### Phase 3: Implement\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+sdp/logs/Lead_T-010_20260408T223256Zb_1775693726.log:29:- Implement the minimum code needed to pass all tests.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+sdp/logs/Lead_T-010_20260408T223256Zb_1775693726.log:34:### Phase 4: Verify & Document\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+sdp/logs/Lead_T-010_20260408T223256Zb_1775693726.log:58:{\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"type\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"message\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"timestamp\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"2026-04-09T00:15:30.202Z\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"role\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"user\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"content\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"# Task T-010@20260408T223256Zb: Wire ollama_health() into the daemon /status endpoint so it appears in the status JSON response; include integration test\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n**Tier:** T2 — Standard (New feature / moderate refactoring)\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n## Instructions\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nRead the project's ADP documentation and understand existing patterns before making changes.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n**ADP Phases:** Explore → Specify → Test → Implement → Verify → Document\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n### Phase 0: Explore\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- Read all files in the affected area of the codebase.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- Identify existing patterns, naming conventions, and architectural decisions.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- Review related tests to understand expected behavior.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- Update progress.md with exploration findings.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n### Phase 1: Specify\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- Write a specification to `specs/t-010@20260408t223256zb-spec.md`.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- Include: problem statement, technical approach, edge cases, acceptance criteria.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- Each acceptance criterion must have a VERIFY command.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n### Phase 2: Test Development\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- Write tests BEFORE implementation, derived from the specification.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- Tests must FAIL before implementation (Red phase).\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- After this phase, test files are LOCKED — do not modify assertions.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n### Phase 3: Implement\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- Implement the minimum code needed to pass all tests.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- One sub-task at a time, commit each logical unit.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- Type hints on all function signatures.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- Follow existing patterns.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n### Phase 4: Verify & Document\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- Run full test suite and quality checks.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- Update CHANGELOG.md, progress.md.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n## Rules\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- No questions — document assumptions in ESCALATIONS.md.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- Do not modify locked test assertions.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- Log new dependencies to ESCALATIONS.md.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- Commit per sub-task: `feat(scope): summary [T-010@20260408T223256Zb]`\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n## Validation\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nRun before final commit:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n```bash\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\npip install -e '.[dev]' && pytest tests/ -x && ruff check src/ tests/ && mypy src/\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n```\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nAll must pass.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"}\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+sdp/logs/Verify_T-018_20260416T043834Z_1776323547.log:16:- Bootstrap hardening: `bootstrap_identity()` is already wired before `FirstBootAnnouncer` in `daemon.py`, with `TestStartupIdentityPersistence` covering both modes\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+sdp/verification/t-012@20260416t043834z-manual-verify.md:15:## Tests / Commands Run\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+sdp/templates/candidates/lead_t2/v001.md:13:Read the project's ADP documentation and understand existing patterns before making changes.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+sdp/templates/candidates/lead_t2/v001.md:15:**ADP Phases:** Explore → Specify → Test → Implement → Verify → Document\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+sdp/templates/candidates/lead_t2/v001.md:17:### Phase 0: Explore\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+sdp/templates/candidates/lead_t2/v001.md:23:### Phase 1: