 shared `Event` data model and follows the `role_is_eligible` contract established in `role_gate.py`. Although `PerformanceIntent` was mentioned in the spec, it is not yet present in the codebase (targeted for T-030), and the use of the `Event` model for these transformations is the correct adaptation for the current project state.\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\n+## Security\\\\\\\\n+No security vulnerabilities or unsafe practices were introduced. The implementation consists of pure-function mathematical transformations on local data structures.\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\n+## Quality\\\\\\\\n+The code quality is high, with clear documentation, clean dataclass abstractions, and robust role-parsing logic. The tests use Pearson correlation to verify complementarity, which is a rigorous approach for validating musical behavior.\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\n+## Issues Found\\\\\\\\n+- None.\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\n+## Verdict: PASS\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\n+## Notes for Lead Agent\\\\\\\\n+The implementation successfully realizes the call-response gating requirement. The adaptation to use the `Event` model in the absence of `PerformanceIntent` is appropriate. Recurring hardening checks for `bootstrap_identity` were also verified to be satisfied in the current daemon startup paths.\\\\\\\"}\\\\n+{\\\\\\\"type\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"message\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\"timestamp\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"2026-04-17T04:06:12.389Z\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\"role\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"assistant\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\"content\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"I'll\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\"delta\\\\\\\":true}\\\\n+{\\\\\\\"type\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"message\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\"timestamp\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"2026-04-17T04:06:12.406Z\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\"role\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"assistant\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\"content\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\" update `progress.md` to mark T-024 as complete and include the relevant logs, ensuring the SDP\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\"delta\\\\\\\":true}\\\\n+\\\\n+codex\\\\n+The dirty state is entirely generated SDP tracking: progress, run logs, notifications, telemetry, and an untracked canonical T-024 verification report 