sdp/prd-pal-2026-agentic-ops-platform.md:1:# PAL 2026 Agentic Operations Platform PRD
sdp/prd-pal-2026-agentic-ops-platform.md:3:**Project:** PromptClaw / PAL 2026
sdp/prd-pal-2026-agentic-ops-platform.md:16:PAL 2026 Phase 1 is already online as a basic inference and operations target:
sdp/prd-pal-2026-agentic-ops-platform.md:20:- PromptClaw has PAL client commands for health, query, smoke tests, baseline summaries, triage, and approval-gated actions.
sdp/prd-pal-2026-agentic-ops-platform.md:23:The current implementation is a useful foundation but is not yet the full "minimal operator involvement" PAL system. This PRD defines the end-to-end build needed to let SDP frontier models implement, verify, and deploy a complete PAL 2026 agentic operations platform.
sdp/prd-pal-2026-agentic-ops-platform.md:28:2. Plan operational workflows using that context.
sdp/prd-pal-2026-agentic-ops-platform.md:43:- `promptclaw/pal_client.py`: stdlib client for PAL router `/health` and `/query`.
sdp/prd-pal-2026-agentic-ops-platform.md:46:- CLI commands:
sdp/prd-pal-2026-agentic-ops-platform.md:52:  - `promptclaw pal agent actions PROJECT_ROOT [--approve ACTION_ID]`
sdp/prd-pal-2026-agentic-ops-platform.md:75:2. Keep Anthony's involvement low: he should mainly approve cost-bearing, credential, restart, shutdown, and destructive actions.
sdp/prd-pal-2026-agentic-ops-platform.md:77:4. Let SDP agents implement and verify this end to end with unit tests, CLI integration tests, and live PAL probes.
sdp/prd-pal-2026-agentic-ops-platform.md:111:The UI/CLI must make the approval boundary concrete. A proposed action should be stored in an artifacted plan, and approval should execute that exact saved action, not a fresh model plan.
sdp/prd-pal-2026-agentic-ops-platform.md:143:Add a typed PAL workflow layer. Each workflow should:
sdp/prd-pal-2026-agentic-ops-platform.md:145:- Have a stable workflow id.
